{Convention for sources:  All sources that are different for MsDos, PC, Cabltest or Phonelink, have a ".MsDOs", ".PC", ".Cbl", or ".Pl" (or combinations thereof) respectively in their file names before ".Plm" or ".ASM".  

Absense of ".MsDos" implies that that file is for GRiD-OS version or common between GRiD-OS & MsDos.  Abscence of .PC in a file name implies that that file is for Compass version or common between Compass and PC.

Convention for Objects:  Their are four kind of prefixes for object files:  

  <none>	for gridlink and phonelink objects without debug
  DBG. 		for gridlink and phonelink objects with debug

objects for modules which are different for MsDos, PC or Cabletest will have an appropriate modifier in the file name for both of the above combinations. 
^EP}

